timeEvent.name: Wedding
timeEvent.description: The first wedding in your community took place on Sunday Afternoon.Both bride and groom came were newcomers to the area. The wedding brought all the community together, with wishes of health and wealth for the future of the community.

timeEvent.name: Welcome to Woolwich
timeEvent.description: You have arrived in the town of Woolwich, on the outskirts of London, England. It has been a long journey and you are far from home. You need to find a place to stay and settle for awhile in this new place.

timeEvent.name: Arsenal Football team moves
timeEvent.description: Now a professional football team, the Arsenal team started by workers at the Gunners factory at the Arsenal moves to Highbury, North London.

timeEvent.name: Haleys Comet
timeEvent.description: The Great Daylight Comet is sighted in the skies over London. Warning to the Inhabitants of the City: Close your windows and keep indoors for the Earth will soon pass through the Tail of the terrible Comet and its poisonous gases will fill the heavens!

timeEvent.name: Jobs For Women at the Arsenal!
timeEvent.description: Since 1872 women had been banned from working in the Arsenal, but with the start of WW1 all our boys are going to war. For the duration of the war women munitions workers are required.

timeEvent.name: Houses for 6 pounds a week
timeEvent.description: You have a cheap place to live, it is a small dark flat near some local shops, the street is a row of rundown cottages near Dairy Lane and Frances Street. Take care of the vagrants and overcrowding in this area.

timeEvent.name: Wellington Cottages
timeEvent.description: You have found a place to live at Wellington Cottages, they are pleasant homes with small gardens full of flowers and vegetables. It feels relatively safe as you hear from your neighbours that the local policemen have moved into this area.

timeEvent.name: Jobs Available in the Arsenal
timeEvent.description: You have found a job at the Arsenal, only available for the men in your community. Houses are available for the Arsenal workers in Plumstead and near the common. Beware temptation in the many public houses after work. It is an eight hour day and overtime to be had.

timeEvent.name: Jobs Available In The Arsenal
timeEvent.description: You have found a job at the Arsenal, only available for the men in your community. Houses are available for the Arsenal workers in Plumstead and near the common. Beware temptation in the many public houses after work. It is an eight hour day and overtime to be had.

timeEvent.name: The last day of buses through the market
timeEvent.description: Finally after decades of complaints about traffic through the market, buses have stopped driving through the market. Some say this has effected the character of the market

timeEvent.name: Prince Charles visits Beresford Square Market
timeEvent.description: Prince of Wales arrives by car to the crowded market square. He steps from the car, greets waiting officials, and shakes hands. Shot from above, the Prince proceeds through the crowded market, escorted by policemen some mounted. The Prince makes his way to the car through a jostling crowd.

timeEvent.name: Prince Charles visits Beresford Square Market
timeEvent.description: Prince of Wales arrives by car to the crowded market square. He steps from the car, greets waiting officials, and shakes hands. Shot from above, the Prince proceeds through the crowded market, escorted by policemen some mounted. The Prince makes his way to the car through a jostling crowd.

timeEvent.name: Prince Charles visits Beresford Square Market
timeEvent.description: Prince of Wales arrives by car to the crowded market square. He steps from the car, greets waiting officials, and shakes hands. Shot from above, the Prince proceeds through the crowded market, escorted by policemen some mounted. The Prince makes his way to the car through a jostling crowd.

timeEvent.name: 36 ton boiler falls off a lorry
timeEvent.description: A huge 36 ton boiler, as a big house fell off a lorry and crashed into an off licence, luckily no one was injured but alot of damage was caused along the High Street.

timeEvent.name: Fire in the Marshes likely to burn for a month!
timeEvent.description: A fire started on the side of the rail track which is likely to burn for a month

timeEvent.name: Queen Mary Comes to Woolwich
timeEvent.description: Queen Mary visits Woolwich, she meets mothers and babies, and nurses as part of the war effort.

timeEvent.name: King George V visits the Barracks
timeEvent.description: The King inspects the Royal Regiment of Artillery... from week-old recruits to fully trained gunner!"

timeEvent.name: Woolwich Boys Make Canoes
timeEvent.description: Woolwich Recreational Institute starts carpentry lessons for teenage boys - building canoes. Boys aged between 16 and 21 using hammers hand drills and saws to build the canoes and then paint them and then they go canoing at Danson Park Lake... Sights like these are a glowing tribute to the much maligned youth of today

timeEvent.name: Woolwich Polytechnic Old Boys Association Reformed
timeEvent.description: Meetings and dances taking place at the Poly or at the Town Hall. Community spirit being much to the fore with chess, debating, drama, Ping-pong (sic), swimming and tennis featuring as well as football and cricket.

timeEvent.name: War Memorial Funding a clubhouse
timeEvent.description: The War Memorial Fund has purchased a house at 72 Footscray Road which was turned into a clubhouse, including a much needed bar, for the Old Shootershillian Association

timeEvent.name: Shooters Hill C C are formed
timeEvent.description: Old Shootershillian Association are now Shooters Hill CC Rugby team, playing in the Kent League.

timeEvent.name: Britain's Christmas Stocking
timeEvent.description: The barracks prepare Christmas Puddings to give out to the Army

timeEvent.name: Couple's cooking classes for married and engaged couples!
timeEvent.description: Cookery classes are available to help both husbands and wife in Woolwich to cook properly.. to break down the old notion that 'indigestion is the cause of wrecked marriages'. Men may find this is the thin end of the wedge.

timeEvent.name: Prince Albert the Duke of York visits to watch army football
timeEvent.description: Duke of York sees British Army score runaway win by 6 goals to 2 over Belgian Army.

timeEvent.name: Midsummer Night's Dream performed at the Rachel McMillan Nursery School
timeEvent.description: The munitions worker's nursery is performing Midsummer's Night Dream.

timeEvent.name: Rachel McMillan Nursery School
timeEvent.description: Nursery opened up in Deptford that mainly with places for munitions workers. The nursery provides a strong emphasis on playing, learning and sleeping outside.

timeEvent.name: Rachel McMillan Nursery School
timeEvent.description: Nursery opened up in Deptford that mainly with places for munitions workers. The nursery provides a strong emphasis on playing, learning and sleeping outside.

timeEvent.name: Midsummer Night's Dream performed at the Rachel McMillan Nursery School
timeEvent.description: The munitions worker's nursery is performing Midsummer's Night Dream.

timeEvent.name: London Suffragette Pageant
timeEvent.description: 66,000 women make a procession through London. By taking their campaign to the streets, the Women's Social and Political Union attract maximum publicity. Identifiable by their purple, white and green colour scheme, the suffragettes are becoming a familiar sight in central London.

timeEvent.name: Folk Club nights taking place
timeEvent.description: Folk clubs are like dog fighting clubs, they're often little known about

timeEvent.name: A big cat spotted in Thamesmead!
timeEvent.description: A black leopard like creature is believed to have been spotted in Thamesmead. The sighting happened at around 3am on Saturday morning (August 9) in Goldfinch Road when a man was woken up by something screeching. The man, who did not want to be named, said: "I saw a black animal rolling on the grass between two trees. I thought to myself, 'Bloody hell! That's the biggest moggy I've ever seen', and then thought, 'It must be a dog'. However, its head was cat-like and its tail was very long.

timeEvent.name: MC Afrikan Boy filmed in Woolwich by Spike Jonze
timeEvent.description: Spike Jonze and M.I.A. visit MC Afrikan Boy on his council estate in Woolwich. Yes that's right, the director of Being John Malcovich and Beastie Boys videos was up a tower block in Woolwich

timeEvent.name: Afirkan Boy is born
timeEvent.description: Olushola Ajose, better known by his stage name "Afrikan Boy" born 28 March 1989 is a grime/Afrobeat MC from Woolwich, London, England, originally from Nigeria.

timeEvent.name: The Biafran War
timeEvent.description: The Biafran war, 1967-1970, resulted in 100,000 military casualties. However, between 500,000 and 2 million Biafran civilians died from starvation during the war. Many Biafrans move to Woolwich to escape the war and find a new home

timeEvent.name: Teenagers hang out at the Dockyard
timeEvent.description: Saturday nights at Woolwich Dockyard teenagers come and hang out.

timeEvent.name: Red Magnets appear in Woolwich
timeEvent.description: A communist theatre group starts in Woolwich

timeEvent.name: The Empire Theatre renamed
timeEvent.description: Woolwich's Theatre is renamed the Woolwich Empire with a capacity of 1,450 seats.

timeEvent.name: Teddy Boy Trouble
timeEvent.description: Police were called to the cinema's around London last night to deal with disturbances among youthful audiences during showings of the film ‘Rock Around the Clock’... 30 policemen arrived. One was knocked between two rows of seats when he tried to stop the dancing. Police and commissionaires ejected about 50 youths. Six youths will appear in court at Woolwich SE today, charged with insulting behaviour outside the Granada cinema, Woolwich, where the film had been shown’.

timeEvent.name: Woolwich women in song
timeEvent.description: 'She works at Woolwich Arsenal Now' - a munition worker's romance' is released

timeEvent.name: New Woolwich Ferry Terminal
timeEvent.description: New terminal for the ferry for cars and lorries

timeEvent.name: Gypsy Moth IV Yacht leaves Woolwich
timeEvent.description: 'Gipsy Moth IV' travels from Woolwich to be permanently berthed at Greenwich, London.

timeEvent.name: New Prefabs in Woolwich
timeEvent.description: Prisoners of war are being brought in to build prefab houses needed as a result of bombed out houses and returning service men to solve the housing crisis, in 10 weeks something like a little suburb will be erected and slotted into place

timeEvent.name: The last London tram leaves from Woolwich
timeEvent.description: A special tram was driven through enormous crowds from Woolwich to New Cross, finally arriving at New Cross depot around 1am on the 6 July.

timeEvent.name: The first MacDonalds in Britain Opens
timeEvent.description: The first ever MacDonalds to open in Britain opens on Powis Street. Woolwich was chosen because it was considered to be a representative English town at the time.

timeEvent.name: Children of Men filmed in Woolwich
timeEvent.description: The apocalypic British film Children of Men was filmed partly in Woolwich.

timeEvent.name: The Woolwich Arsenal finally closes!
timeEvent.description: Th Arsenal finally closes after a long decline.

timeEvent.name: Woolwich Arsenal Station Opens
timeEvent.description: The new terminus of the Docklands Light Railway's London City Airport branch, Woolwich Arsenal station, opened on 10 January 2009.

timeEvent.name: The Royal Military Academy has closed
timeEvent.description: Known as the Shop, the RMA has closed down, taking the jobs with it.

timeEvent.name: Games and holidays stopped at The Shop
timeEvent.description: Due to the war the Royal Military Academy has stopped all sports, games and holidays

timeEvent.name: 860 gunner cadets join The Shop
timeEvent.description: 860 new gunner cadets are recruited to the Royal Military Academy

timeEvent.name: 860 cadets killed in the war
timeEvent.description: 860 cadets have been killed in the war, coincidently the same number as the amount of new cadets that joined the Royal Military Academy in 1916.578 were gunners from the new recruits.

timeEvent.name: Woolwich artillery theatre has burned down
timeEvent.description: The Royal Artillery has a thriving community and much of it is centred around the theatre. Sadly the theatre has caught fire, many people watch as it burns to the grown. They will need to travel further afield now to find entertainment.

timeEvent.name: Woolwich Artillery theatre rebuilt
timeEvent.description: The Woolwich artillery theatre has finally been rebuilt, it has become increasingly popular for local townspeople from across Woolwich, bringing new jobs at the Theatre for the local community not already employed at the Royal Artillery and showing many good plays and concerts.

timeEvent.name: Royal Artillery Bands Training Starts
timeEvent.description: The Bandboys Troop for the military and musical training for Royal Artillary Bands

timeEvent.name: Junior Artillery Band Starts
timeEvent.description: Junior Musicians Troop Artillery Band was established

timeEvent.name: A new stadium opens of Woolwich Common
timeEvent.description: The stadium on Woolwich Common established as a general sports stadium

timeEvent.name: The First Searchlight Tattoo takes Place
The first Police Station Opens in Woolwich
timeEvent.description: The first police station in Woolwich opens, before then the town has been policed by the Arsenal.

timeEvent.name: Jobs are very scarce in Woolwich
Night raids on the Arsenal
timeEvent.description: Night raids by Zeppelins and bombs dropped on artillery place, front parade ground and Mill Lane

timeEvent.name: Night raids
timeEvent.description: Night raids by Zeppelins and bombs dropped on artillery place, front parade ground and Mill Lane

timeEvent.name: Casualties caused by night raids on the Arsenal and Royal Military Academy
Bombs on Woolwich
timeEvent.description: Garrison Church lost its stained glass windows

timeEvent.name: Britain enters World War 2
timeEvent.description: Arms manufacturing is revived at the Arsenal due to the war and more jobs become available

timeEvent.name: Arsenal is a key target in the Blitz
timeEvent.description: Lots of bombing in the blitz (key target)

timeEvent.name: Arsenal is a key target in the Blitz
timeEvent.description: Lots of bombing in the blitz (key target)

timeEvent.name: Gunners manned anti aircraft batteries on Woolwich common
The Arsenal Closes
timeEvent.description: The Arsenal closes, many engineering companies also close that provided jobs and services to the Arsenal

timeEvent.name: Stephen Lawrence stabbed to death
timeEvent.description: Stephen Lawrence who lived and grew up on the Nightingale Estate in Woolwich is stabbed in Eltham.

timeEvent.name: A report occurs about the bad health of the Thames
First motorbike built
timeEvent.description: AJS Motorbikes build their first motorbike, branded with the letter A. The bikes are tested around the streets of Plumstead leaving many young people dreaming of buying a motorbike.

timeEvent.name: Motorbikes supplied to the US
timeEvent.description: Share capital doubles of motorbike industry in Woolwich and jobs increase

timeEvent.name: Motorbikes are no longer made in Woolwich
Ferry carrying 20,000 passengers
timeEvent.description: Every day 20,000 passengers travel on the Woolwich ferry across the Thames to jobs and bringing people to work in Woolwich

timeEvent.name: You have found a place to live and work
timeEvent.description: You have found a place to live on Powis Street above a shop that you are renting out for your business. The city streets are bustling and people come from around London to shop here, the flat is comfortable and safe, you notice people's steps shine white in the sunshine.

timeEvent.name: Arsenal workers live in Plumstead
timeEvent.description: You have found jobs for the men in your community at the Arsenal. There are good houses available for Arsenal workers in this area. You have good neighbours, their wives daughters tend to earn money doing washing and piece work.

timeEvent.name: Explosions on the marshes
timeEvent.description: People living near the marshes are experiencing occassional explosions, followed by crashes that often make the windows shake as far as Shooters Hill. Sometimes windows break but you cant get compensation from the government.

timeEvent.name: Jobs at the Theatre
timeEvent.description: The theatre in Pumstead is very popular and is one of the main employers outside the Arsenal, jobs are available for members of your community.

timeEvent.name: New homes available
timeEvent.description: You have found a new home in the area, many of your neighbours are newly married couples and young families, it feels like a safe place to live.

timeEvent.name: Popular music Hall in Beresford Street
timeEvent.description: Young people in your community enjoy regular nights at the music hall in Beresford Street 14-18 year olds from all around Woolwich come meet each other, dance and watch musicals such as Drummed Out a parody of working at the Arsenal. Many romances begin here.

timeEvent.name: A Walk in the woods
timeEvent.description: Many young people and couples enjoy a walk in the woods beyond the common, you can find pheasants and bluebells and nightingale's singing.

timeEvent.name: sherwood forest starts getting cut down for boats
Max arrives in Woolwich
timeEvent.description: Max finally arrives after the long journey West in Woolwich with his family. They move into a flat on Thomas Street, above his brother Lipman’s grocers shop. They live with their parents David and Annie, who speak no English, and their married nephew, a journeyman tailor waiting to earn enough money to pay for his wife to move to England.

timeEvent.name: Zelda is born
timeEvent.description: he birth of Max’s daughter Zelda is celebrated as the first of a new generation in a new land.

timeEvent.name: Max's youngest brother gets married
timeEvent.description: Max’s youngest brother Velvel marries Fanny. After the ceremony the family returned to Max’s house on Thomas Street, where breakfast and dinner were served and dancing engaged in. A photo of the whole family together in their new home was taken in the yard.

timeEvent.name: Max sets up a workshop
timeEvent.description: Max and his father David set up a Tailor's workshop in Beresford Square. Together they began to learn the language, make friends and business and make a home for the family.

timeEvent.name: Young boys play as the war continues
timeEvent.description: The younger boys in the community play amongst the bombed out buildings in the area.

timeEvent.name: The Blitz causes families to hide in Anderson Shelters
timeEvent.description: A night in the Anderson Shelter becomes nearly a nightly occurence, where huddled together community members sit, drinking condensed milk, gossiping and on a good night with a round of bacon sandwiches.

timeEvent.name: Young gangs spend time wandering about
timeEvent.description: Gangs of youngs lads enjoy the evening by wandering about Woolwich and hanging out near the woods, with their own codes of discipline. Not looking for trouble but sometimes finding it.

timeEvent.name: Young girls often miss school
timeEvent.description: Younger daughters of large families in your community are kept away from school to look after the other children and run chores. They miss their education and their friends but earn money and help around the house

timeEvent.name: Market Day
timeEvent.description: A day in the bustling market on Beresford Square brings people from all over Woolwich on the tram or bus. Lots of calling and shouting, colourful piles of neatly stacked fruit and stalls of slimy fish.

timeEvent.name: The bakers stops using a horse and cart
timeEvent.description: The Royal Artillery bakers to do away with the horse drawn vans and change to diesel vans. The rounds take twice as long, as the driver had to keep getting in and out all the time. Whereas, with the horse the bread was hooked out of the back of the van while it was on the move. The horses are sadly taken to slaughter.

timeEvent.name: War is declared
timeEvent.description: As the war is declared many members of the community worry that the Anderson shelters ordered had not arrived and there would be nowhere to go if an attack began. Many people enlisted and the men began to go off to war.

timeEvent.name: Barrage balloons go up over London
timeEvent.description: 800 or so balloons around London were raised whenever there was risk of a raid and sometimes they stayed up the whole day. On Plumstead Common looking across to the centre of London you could see them as far as the eye could see.

timeEvent.name: A barrage balloon goes up
timeEvent.description: The number of balloons increased, the nearest one is along the railway line on a spare piece of ground, operated by half a dozen RAF Airmen from a large lorry. They live in a nearby Nissen hut and seem to have a cushy life.

timeEvent.name: Road Signs are removed
timeEvent.description: All road signs have been removed and anybody asking directions is automatically suspect. Tales of spies and German parachutists dressed up in nun's clothes abound and young children play spies and track people as street games.

timeEvent.name: The Battle of Britain starts
timeEvent.description: Within a short time the sky is criss-crossed aircraft that look like toys. They move towards the centre of London. Some Barrage balloons are set fire. People watch the aerial battle above. Many of the bombs fall on the Arsenal and the Docks. Looking towards Woolwich and the Arsenal huge fires can be seen up the river.

timeEvent.name: Unexploded bombs dug up
timeEvent.description: As a result of an unexploded bomb finally exploding in Elephant and Castle and killing some children, many unexploded bombs in the Arsenal and city centre are dug up to prevent more casualties.

timeEvent.name: Aircraft crash in Woolwich
timeEvent.description: A Spitfire lost its wing, and crashed in Woolwich. The other plane came down in Plumstead. Both pilots were killed in the crash and there is much damage.

timeEvent.name: Aircraft crash in Woolwich
timeEvent.description: A Spitfire lost its wing, and crashed in Woolwich. The other plane came down in Plumstead. Both pilots were killed in the crash and there is much damage.

timeEvent.name: Children are evacuated
timeEvent.description: Many mothers and children are evacuated out of Woolwich as the Battle of Britain continues.

timeEvent.name: Sweets come off ration
timeEvent.description: Sweets come off ration but there is such a rush for sweets in the shops that the government has to put them back on again as the shops sold out so quickly. The the ration allowance will be gradually increased until people get used to being able to buy them.

timeEvent.name: Airplane crash
timeEvent.description: During a practice for the Queen's Coronation two planes flying in formation collide and begin to spin down to earth, one plane crashed in the Thames and another one in Plumstead. People come out of their houses to watch. At least one pilot loses his life and there are several injuries.

timeEvent.name: Blacketts sells record number of bicycles
timeEvent.description: Blacketts on General Gordon Square sells bicycles to apprentices and workers at the Artillery and Arsenal. Cyclists beware of the tramlines on the busy streets.

timeEvent.name: Picking blackberries on the common
timeEvent.description: Children spend the day on the common with jars in their hands to pick blackberries, they find fossils amongst the stones by knocking them together.

timeEvent.name: Deep snow
timeEvent.description: The snow is so bad that it is piled up so high in people's yards that many people can't get to their outside toilets.

timeEvent.name: The Queen's Coronation
timeEvent.description: Queen Elizabeth 2nd is crowned queen, street parties take place to celebrate and people gather together to watch the coronation on television.

timeEvent.name: Watching the coronation on TV
timeEvent.description: Many members of the community dont have televisions and gather at the Co-Op Hall where a TV is set up and all communities gather together to watch the Queen being crowned.

timeEvent.name: The circus comes to Woolwich
timeEvent.description: As an advertisement for the circus arriving elephants parade down Powis Street. One of the elephants pooed and the trolley bus couldn't drive around it as it was so big! Acouncil lorry eventually came to clear it away.

timeEvent.name: A day put on the Woolwich Ferry
timeEvent.description: Children spend the school holidays, going back and forth on the ferry many times until they get chucked off. They sit on deck and sun theselves or go down to the engine room to see how it all worked.

timeEvent.name: Holiday Outings
timeEvent.description: Many families can't afford holidays, but every year people go on the 'Maybloom Outing' to the seaside with the local social club. Nearly every family in the area belong to either the social or Conservative club. The Maybloom go to Margate by coach and the Conservatives go to Southend by train.

timeEvent.name: Plumstead Baths
timeEvent.description: Many community members use the Public Baths with a rolled up towel and a bar of soap. The attendant stands at the door while the water and says controls the water flow. Take care the water isn't too hot!

timeEvent.name: The Great Depression Begins
timeEvent.description: Still struggling after the effects of WW1, Britain hits a deep financial depression. Many people suffer, lose their jobs and struggle to pay the bills

timeEvent.name: A whole street in the city centre destroyed
timeEvent.description: A whole street is bombed in the centre of Woolwich, killing many families.

timeEvent.name: Max becomes a master tailor
timeEvent.description: Max moves to Mulgrave Place, in Charlton. He has got more work as a master tailor at the Arsenal making uniforms. The family now have eight children and live with a border, a friend of a friend of the family who works as a teacher in the local primary school. The eldest daughter Miriam now works as a clerk at the post office.

timeEvent.name: Solomon's family
timeEvent.description: Max's brother Solomon runs the Boot Makers on Wellington Street, he lives above the shop with his wife and 4 children. All the family get together on Saturdays for a large meal. Its hard to squeeze all the generations and many children into one place, but it makes the family feel at home.

timeEvent.name: Lipman's Success
timeEvent.description: Lipman Jacobs, Max's eldest brother is doing well. He owns two shops, the Boot Makers on Wellington Street and a Grocers on the High Street. He lives above the grocers on the High Street with his wife and three daughters... it is a family of many daughters! His wife and eldest daughter help in the shop.

timeEvent.name: Velvel moves house
timeEvent.description: Max's youngest brother Velvel becomes a tailor like Max. He lives in Creton Street with his wife Fanny, they now have two sons and daughter. They have to be careful living so close to the Dusthole and can't go out much at night.

timeEvent.name: Despite the war business does well
timeEvent.description: The family are keeping their head above water, Lipman moves the Grocers Shop to Beresford Street and gets alot of trade from the women who know work at the factory, buying their groceries on the way home from work.

timeEvent.name: Harder Times
timeEvent.description: Lipman and Solomon decide to close the Boot Makers on Wellington Street.
